    function-checks

    function-checks.Rmd
    library(dfdiffs)

    Motivation

    This vignette takes us through the functions used to compare datasets in the dfdiffs package. The goal of dfdiffs is to answer the following questions:

    1. What rows are here now that weren’t here before?
    2. What rows were here before that aren’t here now?
    3. What values have been changed?

    New Data

    Below are the test base and compare new datasets: base_new_df and compare_new_df

    Base 

    base_new_df |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    1 A 5.5 111 notice
    2 B 9.0 106 admit
    3 C 5.2 109 america
    4 A 4.4 96 try
    5 B 9.1 116 serve
    6 C 6.7 98 because

    Compare 

    compare_new_df |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    1 A 5.5 111 notice
    2 B 9.0 106 admit
    3 C 5.2 109 america
    4 A 4.4 96 try
    5 B 9.1 116 serve
    6 C 6.7 98 because
    1 A 2.8 97 unless
    2 B 8.0 113 believe
    3 C 6.8 111 union

    Changed Data

    Below are the test base and compare changed datasets: base_change_df and compare_change_df

    Base 

    base_change_df |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    1 A 5.5 111 notice
    2 B 9.0 106 admit
    3 C 5.2 109 america
    4 A 4.4 96 try
    5 B 9.1 116 serve
    6 C 6.7 98 because

    Compare 

    compare_change_df |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    1 A 5.5 111 notice
    2 B 3.3 106 admit
    3 C 5.2 109 America
    4 A 4.4 73 NA
    5 B 9.1 116 serve
    6 C 6.7 98 HiStorY

    Single joining (by) column conditions

    1) Two datasets

    • No by columns (only two datasets)
    create_new_data(
   compare = compare_new_df,
   base = base_new_df) |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    1 A 2.8 97 unless
    2 B 8 113 believe
    3 C 6.8 111 union 
    create_deleted_data(
   compare = compare_deleted_df,
   base = base_deleted_df) |> gt::gt(data = )
    id group var_x var_y var_z
    7 D 43.3 338 EVER
    8 E 49.6 347 EFFECT
    9 F 58.7 478 BIT 
    changes <- create_changed_data(
  compare = compare_change_df, 
  base = base_change_df)
    changes$num_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable no_of_differences
    var_x 1
    var_y 1
    var_z 3 
    changes$var_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable rownumber base compare
    var_x 2 9 3.3
    var_y 4 96 73
    var_z 3 america America
    var_z 4 try NA
    var_z 6 because HiStorY

    2) Multiple columns to compare (cols)

    • No by columns (only two datasets) and multiple compare (cols)
    create_new_data(
   compare = compare_new_df,
   base = base_new_df, 
   cols = c('var_x', 'var_z')) |> 
  gt::gt(data = )
    var_x var_z
    2.8 unless
    8 believe
    6.8 union 
    create_deleted_data(
   compare = compare_deleted_df,
   base = base_deleted_df, 
   cols = c('var_x', 'var_y', 'var_z')) |> 
  gt::gt(data = )
    var_x var_y var_z
    43.3 338 EVER
    49.6 347 EFFECT
    58.7 478 BIT 
    changes <- create_changed_data(
  compare = compare_change_df, 
  base = base_change_df, 
  cols = c('var_y', 'var_z'))
    changes$num_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable no_of_differences
    var_y 1
    var_z 3 
    changes$var_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable rownumber base compare
    var_y 4 96 73
    var_z 3 america America
    var_z 4 try NA
    var_z 6 because HiStorY

    3) Single by column

    • Provide a single by column (in this case, we will create the join column using row_number())
    compare <- mutate(compare_new_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
base <- mutate(base_new_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
create_new_data(
   compare = compare,
   base =  base,
   by = "join_var") |> gt::gt(data = )
    join_var id group var_x var_y var_z
    7 1 A 2.8 97 unless
    8 2 B 8 113 believe
    9 3 C 6.8 111 union 
    compare <- mutate(compare_deleted_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
base <- mutate(base_deleted_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
create_deleted_data(
   compare = compare,
   base = base, 
   by = 'join_var') |> 
  gt::gt(data = )
    join_var id group var_x var_y var_z
    7 7 D 43.3 338 EVER
    8 8 E 49.6 347 EFFECT
    9 9 F 58.7 478 BIT 
    compare <- mutate(compare_change_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
base <- mutate(base_change_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
changes <- create_changed_data(
  compare = compare, 
  base = base, 
  by = 'join_var')
    changes$num_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable no_of_differences
    var_x 1
    var_y 1
    var_z 3 
    changes$var_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable join_var base compare
    var_x 2 9 3.3
    var_y 4 96 73
    var_z 3 america America
    var_z 4 try NA
    var_z 6 because HiStorY

    4) Single by column, new column name (by_col)

    • We can also provide a single by column (for unique identifiers) and a new name for the by_col

    • We will create the join column (join_var) using row_number(), then name it join_column

    compare <- mutate(compare_new_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
base <- mutate(base_new_df, 
  join_var = as.character(row_number())) |>  
  dplyr::relocate(join_var, everything())
create_new_data(
   compare = compare,
   base =  base,
   by = "join_var", 
   by_col = 'join_column') |> gt::gt(data = )

    Multiple by column conditions

    7) Multiple by columns

    • Multiple by columns (assuming the columns create a unique identifier).
    create_new_data(
   compare = compare_new_df,
   base = base_new_df,
   by = c("id", "group")) |> gt::gt(data = )
    join id group var_x var_y var_z
    1-A 1 A 2.8 97 unless
    2-B 2 B 8 113 believe
    3-C 3 C 6.8 111 union 
    create_deleted_data(
  compare = compare_deleted_df,
  base = base_deleted_df,
  by = c("id", "group")) |> gt::gt(data = )
    join id group var_x var_y var_z
    7-D 7 D 43.3 338 EVER
    8-E 8 E 49.6 347 EFFECT
    9-F 9 F 58.7 478 BIT 
    changes <- create_changed_data(
  compare = compare_change_df, 
  base = base_change_df,
  by = c("id", "group"))
    changes$num_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable no_of_differences
    var_x 1
    var_y 1
    var_z 3 
    changes$var_diffs |> gt::gt(data = )
    variable join base compare
    var_x 2-B 9 3.3
    var_y 4-A 96 73
    var_z 3-C america America
    var_z 4-A try NA
    var_z 6-C because HiStorY

    8) Multiple by columns, new column name (by_col)

    We can provide multiple by columns, a new by_col, and no cols
